<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COUNTY NEWS ROUNDUP: SANTA PAULA; 
</P>
<P>
YOUTH HOSPITALIZED WITH STAB WOUNDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 17-year-old youth was found staggering and bleeding from multiple stab wounds 
early Sunday morning in Santa Paula, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
The victim, Manuel Ortiz, was in critical but stable condition Sunday after 
surgery for wounds in the abdomen and chest, said Cecelia Moore, nursing 
supervisor at Santa Paula Memorial. 
</P>
<P>
Santa Paula police officers responding to a 2:20 a.m. call about fighting 
discovered the victim bleeding and staggering south on Ojai Street, said 
dispatcher Lesley Dybrack. No motive for the attack was known, Dybrack said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
