<HEADLINE>
<P>
PUPPIES GET PUT THROUGH THEIR PACES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
On Sunday, a dog day of its own, about 40 young canines, their tongues 
sometimes lolling, took part in guide dog trials on a grassy lawn in Sylmar. 
The Labrador, German shepherd and golden retriever puppies, adopted and trained 
by volunteers for 15 to 18 months, were being returned to International Guiding 
Eyes Inc., a nonprofit organization for the blind, for further instruction. But 
first, they showed off their prowess by running an obstacle course filled with 
such distractions as a hot dog, a live burro and a ceramic dog. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
