Your editorial placed human life above animal life. I congratulate you on 
making the only possible moral decision. 
</P>
<P>
However, since human life is more valuable than animal life, it requires that 
we ask and answer this question: What is the moral justification for animal 
rights groups spending millions of dollars on saving experimental animals while 
human beings die of hunger, war and pestilence? 
</P>
