<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA050790-0016 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 215114 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
May 7, 1990, Monday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 6; Column 3; Letters Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
81 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANIMAL RIGHTS MOVEMENT AND MEDICAL EXPERIMENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The weakness of your argument lies in couching it in "either-or" terms. 
</P>
<P>
You view life as a hierarchy. It's not -- it's a monarchy. When we seek to 
advance humankind by experimenting, inflicting pain, and, ultimately killing a 
fellow creature we do so by sacrificing all semblance of human character. We 
are called as stewards, not despots. To advocate that these must die that we 
may live is the mentality that has turned the earth into a dunghill. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD DUNKERLY 
</P>
<P>
Whittier 
</P>
</TEXT>
