<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO SPORTS ET CETERA: UCSD WINS WATER POLO TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The UC San Diego women's water polo team capped its first undefeated season 
with its second national championship Sunday by defeating UC Davis, 9-3, in the 
USA Collegiate Nationals at Brown University. 
</P>
<P>
The Tritons, the top-seeded team, finished 26-0-1. 
</P>
<P>
Brenda Reiton led the way with three goals. Jamie Dailey added two goals. 
Reiton, who led UCSD in the tournament with 16 goals, and and Jefi Paulsen were 
named to the All-American team. Dailey was selected to the second team, and 
Kristen Larson was honorable mention. 
</P>
<P>
VINTAGE AUTO RACING 
</P>
<P>
Fred Cziska of Pacifica won the feature class -- the A &amp; B Super Sport and 
Formula A -- at the second Rodger Ward Invitational in the San Diego Jack 
Murphy Stadium parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
In a 1971 Can-Am Shadow, Cziska, 48, won with an average speed of 108.5 miles 
per hour. Cziska, an auto dealership manager, has been racing vintage cars for 
five years.BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
Three school records were set as San Diego State completed a four-game sweep of 
Colorado State with a 27-10 Western Athletic Conference rout in Fort Collins. 
</P>
<P>
The Aztecs set single-game records for runs (27) and hits (29). 
</P>
<P>
Brian Grebeck would have tied several others for most hits in a game by going 
five for seven with three runs batted in, but Derrick Vineyard had six singles 
and a walk in eight trips. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU (37-20, 17-7) moved into a first-place tie with Wyoming. Brigham Young is 
a half-game back at 16-7-1. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. International jumped to an early three-run lead but fell to UCLA, 6-3, in 
Westwood. Kyle Sebach (2-4) was the loser for USIU (13-41). 
</P>
<P>
GOLF 
</P>
<P>
San Diego State finished fourth in the Western Athletic Conference men's 
championships at Texas El Paso. Brigham Young won the tournament at 858. SDSU 
shot 897. 
</P>
<P>
SDSU's Doug Carney finished seventh at 216, nine strokes behind champion Paul 
Stankowski of Texas El Paso. 
</P>
<P>
CREW 
</P>
<P>
The University of San Diego men's team was fifth behind winner UCLA in the 
varsity race of the Newport Regatta. 
</P>
<P>
UC San Diego's women's team won the McNeish Trophy for most points (377) in the 
Oxnard All-American Regatta, considered the championship of Southern 
California. 
</P>
<P>
UCSD won the varsity eight for the first time in 7:00.2 over the 2,00-meter 
course. 
</P>
</TEXT>
