<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Partying With Arsenio, Peeples: Arsenio Hall will produce a new show to follow 
his hit television talk show. 
</P>
<P>
The nightly half-hour variety program, called "The Party Machine With Nia 
Peeples," is set to debut next January. Peeples, an actress and singer, 
appeared on the TV series "Fame" and has recently released the album "Nothin' 
but Trouble." "The Party Machine" will showcase live musical performances, 
comedians, music videos and in-studio dancing. The program will be syndicated 
by Paramount. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
