<HEADLINE>
<P>
PANAMA RITES HELD FOR INVASION DEAD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
PANAMA CITY 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Archbishop Marcos G. McGrath of Panama attended a burial service Sunday for 123 
people killed during the U.S. invasion whose bodies were exhumed from a mass 
grave and identified by relatives. 
</P>
<P>
Officials said the bodies, which included several children, had been buried in 
green plastic and canvas bags used by the U.S. armed forces. They were killed 
in the Dec. 20 invasion that ousted strongman Gen. Manuel A. Noriega, the 
officials added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
