<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COAST COLLEGE WINS NEWPORT REGATTA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Orange Coast College, which took first in the junior varsity eight and the 
novice eight, was the overall champion Sunday at the 25th Newport Harbor 
Regatta. 
</P>
<P>
The OCC junior varsity eight boat won in 6 minutes 1 second. UCLA was second in 
6:05.7. The OCC novice boat won in 6:10. UC Santa Barbara was second (6:13.7). 
</P>
<P>
OCC scored 24 points to win the P.A. Palmer Cup, which goes to the overall 
winner. UCLA (19 points) was second, followed by Santa Barbara (14) and Santa 
Clara (13). 
</P>
</TEXT>
