<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Soviets Importing U.S. Chickens: The Soviet Union began buying American-grown 
broilers last fall for the first time in years, the Agriculture Department 
reported, and looks likely to edge out Japan this year as the leading 
chicken-export market for U.S. producers. While 1989 sales involved only about 
26 million pounds, Moscow has bought about 260 million pounds so far this year, 
which the department valued at more than $100 million. 
</P>
</TEXT>
