<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN COURT: A SUMMARY OF SOUTHERN CALIFORNIA-RELATED BUSINESS LITIGATION 
DEVELOPMENTS DURING THE PAST WEEK. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MGM/UA Sued Over Movie Distribution: MGM/United Artist Pictures Inc. was sued 
in Los Angeles Superior Court for allegedly failing to use its "best efforts" 
to distribute the film "Mind Games" in the United States and Canada. 
</P>
<P>
The suit, filed by MTA/Persik Productions and MTA Productions Inc., claims 
MGM/UA bought the distribution rights but never intended to diligently promote 
the movie. The suit seeks more than $2.6 million, claiming MGM/UA has a 
"pattern" of not properly promoting some films because it is contractually 
obliged to give movies to CBS/Fox Co. for release as home videocassettes. 
(Filed April 30, 1990. Case No. C759894) 
</P>
</TEXT>
