<P>
BRIEFLY: CONSUMER NEWS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mortgage Rates at Year's Peak: Fixed-rate home mortgages are currently 
averaging 10.67%, their highest rate in nearly a year, according to a national 
survey released by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp. It was the highest rate 
since fixed-rate mortgages averaged 10.69% last May 19. They averaged 10.56% 
last week. On one-year adjustable-rate mortgages, lenders asked an average 
initial rate of 8.62% last week, up from 8.56% the week before. 
</P>
</TEXT>
