<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR THE RECORD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CURATOR'S ROLE -- A recent Calendar story about the resignation of Lucinda 
Barnes as associate curator of Newport Harbor Art Museum misstated her role in 
organizing the fall 1990 exhibition, "Tony Cragg: Investigations Into Chaos." 
Barnes is writing one of the catalogue essays; former chief curator Paul 
Schimmel and assistant curator Marilu Knode are co-curating the exhibit. 
</P>
