<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL; 
</P>
<P>
$250,000 MOTEL FIRE NEAR DISNEYLAND UNDER INVESTIGATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An early morning fire swept through two units of a motel near Disneyland, 
causing $250,000 damage, authorities said today. 
</P>
<P>
Fire officials are still investigating the cause of the blaze that broke out 
shortly after 4 a.m. at the Saga Motel in the 1600 block of South Harbor 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
No injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
Anaheim Fire Department Division Chief Ron Hamric said an occupant of one of 
the burned units called 911 after smelling smoke in his room. 
</P>
<P>
Forty Anaheim firefighters, assisted by a unit from the Orange Fire Department, 
took 14 minutes to control the fire, Hamric said. 
</P>
<P>
Hamric said quick work by firefighters prevented an additional $2 million in 
damage. 
</P>
<P>
"We were lucky that everything worked well," Hamric said. "The smoke alarms 
sounded . . . and we got there right in time to prevent a disaster." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Brief; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
